page.title: 13Wild life on the estuary.
page.content: { {Birds seen on the estuary} Oyster catcher,Herring gulls,Black headed gull,Cormorant,Heron,Mallard, Shell duck,Lapwing,Canada geese. These birds are on the estuary because there is an abundance of food. There is a huge cockle bed.On the marsh there are Eider ducks,Lug worms, Sea potato,netted whelk and the masked crab. {Birds of prey Buzzards,Twany owl,Barn owl,kestrel, sparrow hawk, {Wild animals Rabbits,foxes,badgers,field mice. {Trees Oak,beech,sycamore,horse chesnut, silver birch,hawthorn.
